explains: n. （机构、组织等的）开端，创始

sentences.en: The club has grown rapidly since its inception in 1990.
sentences.cn: 这个俱乐部自从1990年成立以来发展迅速。

sentences.en: Since its inception the company has produced 53 different aircraft designs.
sentences.cn: 该公司自成立以来已经设计出53种不同的飞行器。

sentences.en: The issue is not development time, but rather the full time between project inception and delivery.
sentences.cn: 这个问题不是开发时间，而是从项目开始到交付的全部时间。
